Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.67,0:00:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, Corrina."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.80,0:00:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why are the letters from you so short?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.64,0:00:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"Like Eupolis the astrol… astrologer,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.56,0:00:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you throw my heart into disarray."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.15,0:00:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"The gold of Idas so fades."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.57,0:00:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,-"The craftsman of Gallonius…"\N-Just stop already.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.24,0:00:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told you\Nthere is no need to read any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.99,0:00:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.20,0:00:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're done here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.21,0:00:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Just leave already.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.71,0:00:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.79,0:00:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I offended you in some way?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.71,0:00:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone without proper Latin pronunciation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.09,0:00:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,has no right to read books to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.09,0:00:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize. I will be more careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.72,0:00:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,FRIEDRICH EMMANUEL SCHOOL\NOF MUNICH UNIVERSITY
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.92,0:02:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You were scolded pretty harshly\Nback at the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.30,0:02:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Chin up, business management major\NKarl Neuman.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.14,0:02:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.76,0:03:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know about me? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.10,0:03:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Lotte Frank,\Na cultural anthropology major.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.81,0:03:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you also work part-time\Nreading books for that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.11,0:03:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I take care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.74,0:03:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He only lets male students\Nread books to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.66,0:03:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the Tuesday boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.49,0:03:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other days, other students
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.70,0:03:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,read books for that nearly blind man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.62,0:03:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what do you think about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.42,0:03:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That mysterious man of wealth,\NHans Georg Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.38,0:03:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not really sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.51,0:03:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I only jumped at the job\Nbecause the pay was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.18,0:03:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard all the rumors about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.39,0:03:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,With one call from the estate,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.98,0:03:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he can freely control the stocks\Nof any company in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.02,0:03:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He's known as\Nthe Howard Hughes of Bavaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.40,0:03:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He has no family or anyone close to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.95,0:03:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet his fortune keeps growing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.66,0:04:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think\Nhe plans to do with that money?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.12,0:04:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's an even bigger mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.87,0:04:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Another one of his aliases\Nis the Vampire of Bavaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.12,0:04:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Vampire?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.92,0:04:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When the bell rings at 2:00 a.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.96,0:04:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he rides a coffin-like car\Naccompanied by his butler
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.96,0:04:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and heads to town in the dead of night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.63,0:04:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a scene\Nout of a gothic horror story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.64,0:04:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't he just taking a walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.93,0:04:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll figure out soon enough\Nif it's just a walk or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.19,0:04:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Figure out? Are you…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.56,0:04:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for my research thesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.65,0:04:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Psychology of Bavarian Financiers\Nfrom the Middle Ages and Today."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.99,0:04:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll definitely be a great sample.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.86,0:04:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, while you were at it,\Nyou looked into me too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.87,0:04:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I only looked up your name and major.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.41,0:04:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't be upset\Nthat you got yelled at by Schuwald, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.21,0:04:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He says awful things\Nto the other students too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.46,0:04:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm used to being hit and yelled at.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.97,0:04:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're used to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.97,0:05:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I went through a lot,\Nmoving from one foster home to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh right, you didn't attend\None of the local preparatory high schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.14,0:05:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So you actually did look into me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.73,0:05:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.31,0:05:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.11,0:05:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I enrolled in Munich University\Nbecause I thought I could meet my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.16,0:05:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother is in Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.41,0:05:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, did you meet her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It doesn't matter now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.50,0:05:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.17,0:05:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're finally near her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.00,0:05:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know her name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.88,0:05:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.34,0:05:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is her name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.55,0:05:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.55,0:05:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.09,0:05:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I'm interested,\NI figure things out one way or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.35,0:05:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Margot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.77,0:05:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.64,0:05:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you know that much,\Nyou can find her right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.52,0:05:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Go see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.82,0:05:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll be thrilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.53,0:06:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, it doesn't matter now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.32,0:06:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.33,0:06:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.37,0:06:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"The sprint of the chestnut-colored horse
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.21,0:06:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,gathered thunderclaps in my blood."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.42,0:06:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"It caused great waves…"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.88,0:06:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't bear to listen any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.59,0:06:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I only love that which is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.05,0:06:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't bear to listen anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.52,0:06:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell me\Nsomething so important?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.90,0:06:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked up your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.19,0:06:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.82,0:06:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you it doesn't matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.91,0:06:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, is there any way\NI can be of help to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.87,0:06:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, but it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.96,0:06:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.17,0:06:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.05,0:07:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,About Hans Schuwald's movements at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.72,0:07:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-you said you'd figure him out, right?\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.80,0:07:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I come with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.35,0:07:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.93,0:07:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be reassuring for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.56,0:07:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.23,0:07:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Supernatural Phenomenon Club's\Nbiggest scoop ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.07,0:07:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I have my doubts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.40,0:07:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, there's no doubt\Nthis poem was written in 1502
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.16,0:07:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,by Bishop Gropius,\None of the university founders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.00,0:07:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This one section is the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.54,0:07:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"In the second-to-last\Nof the fullest years,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.09,0:07:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the Thursday boy will visit this place."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.88,0:07:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"The books shall be enveloped in flame,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.01,0:07:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the entire world\Nshall be enveloped in sadness."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.68,0:07:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.10,0:07:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.77,0:07:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,See here?\N"The second-to-last of the fullest years."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.81,0:07:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 1996.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.15,0:07:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.31,0:08:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.90,0:08:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"Fullest years"\Nis referring to leap years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.94,0:08:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The only leap years this century\Nare this year and 2000.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.74,0:08:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"…visit this place.\NThe books shall be enveloped in flame."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.16,0:08:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The part with the books in this place\Nis implying this university will burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.50,0:08:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what is "the Thursday boy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.58,0:08:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The word donnerstag, meaning Thursday,\Ncomes from donner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.09,0:08:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, thunder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.59,0:08:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the god of thunder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.22,0:08:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a big stretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.22,0:08:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.01,0:08:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's our next newsletter's feature!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.68,0:08:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine with putting it in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.44,0:08:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but who'd believe 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.02,0:08:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that a god of destruction\Nwould come to this university?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.04,0:08:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vampire of Bavaria? Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.62,0:08:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the truth after we chased after\Nhis mysterious loitering?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.88,0:09:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.25,0:09:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet. He's coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.93,0:09:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.34,0:09:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.47,0:09:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, get home safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.64,0:09:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.60,0:09:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.03,0:09:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's stop this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.28,0:09:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this isn't somewhere\Nto bring a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.24,0:09:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You should leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.08,0:09:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"I only love that which is beautiful."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.79,0:09:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.21,0:09:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.21,0:09:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,just how despicable this man is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.72,0:09:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.14,0:10:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for women,\Nyou're in the wrong place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.85,0:10:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already retired long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.19,0:10:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.74,0:10:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When you visit someone,\Nyou should introduce yourself first.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.99,0:10:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.96,0:10:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.12,0:10:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like you're a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.42,0:10:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.71,0:10:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I do part-time work\Nat Hans Schuwald's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.01,0:10:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.55,0:10:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know\Nwhy Mr. Hans Schuwald comes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.64,0:10:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He comes here for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.31,0:10:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Or that's what I'd like to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.69,0:10:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But apparently he can't get it up anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.24,0:10:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He comes to give me money.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.28,0:10:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.32,0:10:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.91,0:10:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went to him and told him my name,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.74,0:11:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,he started crying and apologized.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.08,0:11:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, he threw me away like trash\Nafter making me birth a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.75,0:11:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, could it be\Nthat you're Hans Schuwald's child?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.01,0:11:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-But--\N-You're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.26,0:11:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You're…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.80,0:11:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.05,0:11:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was in the papers a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.10,0:11:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"Former prostitute…"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.69,0:11:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Former prostitute\NMargot Langer was killed."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"Culprit still at large."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.27,0:11:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,His mother is already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.53,0:11:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You took advantage of that,\Nposing as my mother, Margot Langer,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.49,0:11:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,taking away large sums of money\Nfrom Hans Schuwald. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.79,0:11:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.50,0:11:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He pays me,\Nknowing that I'm not the real one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.75,0:11:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows the real Margot\Nhe should pay no longer exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.43,0:12:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so this is his way of atonement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.26,0:12:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, money, and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.77,0:12:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To a man who has only lived with money,\Nthis is the only way he knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.02,0:12:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He speaks like he's above everyone,\Nbut people are all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.69,0:12:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You could go up to the old geezer,\Nsay you're his son,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.03,0:12:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and get that enormous fortune of his.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.04,0:12:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your point?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.79,0:12:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're calling me a liar,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.04,0:12:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm not too sure about you either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.26,0:12:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another person
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.80,0:12:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,who's calling himself his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.76,0:12:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?!\N-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.76,0:12:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He came here just like you did\Nand said the exact same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.23,0:12:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.27,0:12:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.98,0:12:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.11,0:12:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy was lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.32,0:12:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know which of you is the liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.95,0:13:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You both look like fakes to me though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.62,0:13:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.08,0:13:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.66,0:13:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You all have your own day of the week\Nwhen you read books to Schuwald, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.67,0:13:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy was one of them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.17,0:13:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I believe it was
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.76,0:13:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the Thursday boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.14,0:13:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell her\Nyou're the real one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.85,0:13:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.23,0:13:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've moved between many foster homes,\None after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.52,0:13:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So of course, I've been through a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.90,0:13:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But my current foster parents\Nhave been really good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.57,0:13:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I could never thank them enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.32,0:13:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I wanted to\Ntry meeting my real parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.87,0:13:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,By learning how despicable\Nmy real father is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.00,0:13:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I could learn to\Ntruly love my current foster parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.92,0:13:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.89,0:14:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen the Thursday boy before?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.56,0:14:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thursdays are my days off, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.35,0:14:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've gone to get\Nsomething I forgot before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.44,0:14:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You've seen him before? What's he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.02,0:14:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.78,0:14:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He was blond,\Nwith very pretty facial features.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.66,0:14:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,MONDAY
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.16,0:14:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this Thursday boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.46,0:14:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a man\Npretending to be me at this university.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.09,0:14:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Karl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.34,0:14:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to what your mother has to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.22,0:14:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this money\Nand ride train number five.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.22,0:14:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get off at the eighth station,\Nan old lady named Marta will be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.14,0:14:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.69,0:14:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you. I can't go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.36,0:15:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the police chasing you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.28,0:15:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'll stay with you too.\N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.11,0:15:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stay with me,\Nyou'll be put into an orphanage here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.49,0:15:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stay,\Nyou'll be called a prostitute's boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.37,0:15:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Go now. Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.92,0:15:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,-What about Dad?\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.08,0:15:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad's a person named\NHans Georg Schuwald, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.80,0:15:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Who told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.72,0:15:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Vera from across the street was saying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.47,0:15:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He's super rich, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.85,0:15:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She said that I was thrown away by my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.56,0:15:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't thrown away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.94,0:15:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll go stay with Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.53,0:15:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.03,0:15:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.70,0:15:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When you grow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.99,0:15:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If you still want to meet him as an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.08,0:15:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But you mustn't want anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.75,0:15:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't resent him if he treats you coldly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.12,0:15:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.84,0:16:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I don't resent him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.10,0:16:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.19,0:16:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This was from your dad\Nwhen you were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.57,0:16:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, I figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.82,0:16:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out who the Thursday boy is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.99,0:16:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.33,0:16:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Edmund Fahren.\NHe's in the Faculty of Literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.75,0:16:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He's definitely reading books\Nfor Schuwald on Thursdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.54,0:16:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Edmund Fahren…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.26,0:16:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He should be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.67,0:16:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The lecture in this classroom just ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.60,0:16:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.06,0:16:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We're looking for Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.10,0:16:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Oh, him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.85,0:17:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Edmund here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.98,0:17:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Edmund?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.32,0:17:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.65,0:17:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.74,0:17:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.16,0:17:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That was unfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.29,0:17:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's only a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.29,0:17:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll grab that fraud\Nby the neck soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.46,0:17:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who will inherit\NSchuwald's enormous fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.84,0:17:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.71,0:17:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.09,0:17:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care about the inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.34,0:17:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.59,0:17:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He can squeeze out\Nas much of Schuwald's money as he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.43,0:17:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.35,0:17:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.06,0:17:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But that student named Edmund Fahren
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.31,0:17:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is saying he's my mother's son.\NI can't let that slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.95,0:17:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,TUESDAY
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.07,0:17:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"As your flowery silken hem\Nfluttered in the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.87,0:17:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a mockingbird was calling out to me\Nin my heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.96,0:18:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't say anything today,\NMr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.09,0:18:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.34,0:18:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I have yelled at you so many times.\NWhy haven't you quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.39,0:18:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because the pay is nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.73,0:18:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.56,0:18:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.23,0:18:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is money all you can talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.16,0:18:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.78,0:18:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are your parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.41,0:18:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was raised by foster parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.29,0:18:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.00,0:18:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for my rude question.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.38,0:18:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you want to meet your real parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.09,0:18:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.14,0:18:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.14,0:19:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems the boy who appeared this time\Nis the real deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.23,0:19:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not after my money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.77,0:19:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,"He"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.69,0:19:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I was just talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.19,0:19:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.62,0:19:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and also…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.45,0:19:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Latin…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.50,0:19:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,has gotten better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.88,0:19:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.84,0:19:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,WEDNESDAY
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.97,0:19:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems Edmund Fahren\Nis absent today too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.68,0:19:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, I bet he's just lying in bed\Nwith a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.52,0:19:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to rush.\NTomorrow is Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.27,0:19:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll show up to his job at Schuwald's.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.69,0:19:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.61,0:19:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll rip off his disguise\Nright in front of Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.62,0:20:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.24,0:20:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's totally destroy him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.33,0:20:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,THURSDAY
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.37,0:20:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not showing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.37,0:20:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost an hour has passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.38,0:20:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If he has a cold, we could confront him\Nwhile he's bedridden.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.67,0:20:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.51,0:20:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case,\Nhow about we barge into his lodgings?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.05,0:20:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You've even looked into Fahren's address?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.06,0:20:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,204…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.98,0:20:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,204.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.56,0:20:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.15,0:20:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.90,0:21:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,FRIDAY
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.78,0:21:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This complicates things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.65,0:21:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone on campus\Nis talking about Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.74,0:21:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe he committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.66,0:21:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The school paper\Nhas his suicide note in it too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.50,0:21:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can no longer deceive others."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.92,0:21:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This must mean…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.00,0:21:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.21,0:21:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretending to be Schuwald's son\Nand getting close to him
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.09,0:21:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,must have been eating at his conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.30,0:21:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If he was so troubled that he'd die,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.18,0:21:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he shouldn't have done it\Nin the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.69,0:21:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, yesterday must've been tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.31,0:21:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.65,0:22:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The police kept questioning me\Nabout the situation all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.40,0:22:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the day off today\Nfrom the book reading job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.12,0:22:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Schuwald was incredibly depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.37,0:22:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Karl, let me introduce you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.29,0:22:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Friday guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.41,0:22:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.87,0:22:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, I'm Karl Neuman\Nfrom the economics department.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.59,0:22:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Johan Liebert from the law department.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.75,0:02:38.93,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(700,700)\pos(360,340)}Thursday's Boy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.15,0:23:53.59,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1000,0)\pos(360,340)}The Secret Woods
